text: John Wussow (February 16, 1879 - May 19, 1920) was an American gymnast. He competed in four events at the 1904 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1879 births Category:1920 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Milwaukee
